               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-168-person1659">
                  JOSEPH 
                  MARKHAM
               <interp inst="t18310217-168-person1659" type="surname" value="MARKHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-168-person1659" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-168-person1659" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Williams'-mews, Hampstead-road, and am <rs id="t18310217-168-viclabel1012" type="occupation">driver of the cab</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-168-victim1658 t18310217-168-viclabel1012"></join>, No. 194. On the 18th of January I went into a chemist's-shop, No. 260, <placeName id="t18310217-168-crimeloc1013">Tottenham-court-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-168-crimeloc1013" type="placeName" value="Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-168-crimeloc1013" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-168-off1010 t18310217-168-crimeloc1013"></join>, and left my cab at the door, with a cloak on the seat; I saw the prisoner pass, and take the cloak - I ran out; he turned into Russell-street, and threw it down - I took it up, and followed him; I lost sight of him for about a minute; when I saw him again he was still running - I have no doubt that he is the man; I took him - the Police-constable came and took him; he said he was very sorry for it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Was any body with you when he made this statement? A. The Policeman was; it was not a very dark night - it was between ten and eleven o'clock; he was taken within one hundred yards of the spot.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-168-person1660">
                  JOSEPH 
                  STANNARD
               <interp inst="t18310217-168-person1660" type="surname" value="STANNARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-168-person1660" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-168-person1660" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I heard a cry of Stop thief! I ran, saw the prisoner running very fast, and a number of people after him, up Russell-street, Tavistock-street, and round into Tottenham-court-road - he told me he had had no victuals the whole of the day, and he would starve before he would do any thing of the kind again.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. He seemed very contrite? A. Yes - he was quite cut up about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310217-168-verdict1014" type="verdictDescription">
